Build a production-ready Astro website for an immigration consulting business (Cachinavisa / Ivy Consulting), inspired by the structure of https://newgvisa.com/, but NOT copying its content or branding.

========================
GOAL
========================

Create a content-driven immigration website focused on:

- Blog/article system (primary)
- Category and tag archives
- SEO structure
- Service pages
- Consultation conversion (contact CTA)

This is NOT a simple corporate landing page.

It should behave like a content-heavy knowledge site with ongoing article publishing.

Visual design does NOT need to match 1:1, but:

- Information architecture
- Page types
- SEO coverage
- Content structure

should be similar in concept.

========================
CORE PRINCIPLES
========================

1. Content-first, not company-first
- Homepage must show latest blog posts (NOT just company intro)
- Blog system is the core of the site
- Service pages are secondary

2. DO NOT copy content
- Do NOT copy text, articles, or branding from newgvisa
- All content must be original
- You may replicate structure, topics, and search intent

3. SEO-oriented architecture
- Clean URL structure
- Strong internal linking
- Category and tag system
- Pagination

4. Markdown-first content system
- Blog posts and service pages must be written in Markdown or MDX
- Easy to scale and update later

========================
TECH STACK
========================

- Astro (latest version)
- TypeScript
- Astro Content Collections
- Markdown / MDX support
- Static site generation

